<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/prefs_main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="plonetheme.jqueryui">

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="prefs_configlet_main">

    <h1 class="documentFirstHeading"
        i18n:translate="heading_theme_settings">Theme settings</h1>

    <a href=""
        class="link-parent"
        tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/plone_control_panel"
        i18n:translate="label_up_to_plone_setup">
            Up to Site Setup
    </a>

    <p i18n:translate="description_theme_settings" class="discreet">
        Use this control panel to manage jqueryui themes.
    </p>
    <h2><a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/context/absolute_url}/@@collective.jqueryuithememanager-select">Select a theme</a></h2>
    <p>Themes are not selected when you create or import them. You must select one theme !</p>
    <h2><a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/context/absolute_url}/@@jqueryui-import-theme">Import a theme</a></h2>
    <p>Here you can import a theme from a zip file built on <a href="http://www.jqueryui.com/themeroller">jqueryui.com/themeroller</a></p>
    <h2><a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/context/absolute_url}/@@collective.jqueryuithememanager-custom-controlpanel">Create a theme</a></h2>
    <p>Create your theme with this form, no need to go on jqueryui website.</p>
    <h2><a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${view/context/absolute_url}/@@collective.jqueryuithememanager-load-default-themes">Load default themes</a></h2>
    <p>JQueryUI provide default themes. Just by clicking the link below you will get all default themes that fit with your version.</p>

</div>

</body>
</html>